{"info": {"author": "mikeee", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6"], "description": "# baidu-tr-free ![Python3.6 package](https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/workflows/Python3.6%20package/badge.svg)![Codecov](https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/workflows/Codecov/badge.svg)[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/baidu-tr-free.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/baidu-tr-free)\n\nBaidu translate for free -- local cache plus throttling. Let's hope it lasts.\n\n### Broken or not\n![Python3.6 package](https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/workflows/Python3.6%20package/badge.svg): failing indicates `broken`. In case of `failing`, try the following workaround: log in to https://passport.baidu.com first. Then use the Chrome browser to visit https://fanyi.baidu.com/v2transapi?from=en&to=zh&query=test, press F12 and then ctr-R (or any method) to open devtools' Network tab and reload. Locate `https://fanyi.baidu.com/v2transapi?from=en&to=zh` and obtain the BAIDUID and token strings in the headers. Plug in the BAIDUID and token strings to lines 66-67 in the  file `bdtr.py.`\n\n### Fixed\n* Text longer than 30 characters can be handled now.\n* Auto-fetching BAIDUID and TOKEN\n\n### Installation\n```pip install -U baidu-tr-free```\nor\n* install (pip or whatever) necessary requirements, e.g. ```\npip install js2py requests_cache jsonpath_rw``` or ```\npip install -r requirements.txt```\n* Drop the file bdtr.py in any folder in your PYTHONPATH (check with import sys; print(sys.path)\n  * Several valid TOKEN/BAIDUID are included.\n* or clone the repo (e.g., ```git clone https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free.git``` or download https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/archive/master.zip and unzip) and change to the baidu-tr-free folder and do a ```\npython setup.py develop```\n\n### Usage\nLog in to https://passport.baidu.com  using Chrome: `bdtr` needs the cookies info (`BAIDUID`) from the Chrome browser on baidu.com.\n\n```\nfrom bdtr import bdtr\nprint(bdtr('hello world'))  # -> '\u4f60\u597d\uff0c\u4e16\u754c'\nprint(bdtr('hello world', to_lang='de'))  # ->'Hallo Welt'\nprint(bdtr('hello world', to_lang='jp'))  # ->'\u30cf\u30ed\u30fc\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9'\n```\n`to_lang='fr'` does not seem to work tho.\n\n### Validation and Pressure Tests\n* pip install pytest\n* pytest\n  * Average delay for throttling set to 0.6 s, ajdust as needed\n\n### Acknowledgments\n\n* Thanks to everyone whose code was used\n* JS_SIGN (javascript code for signing) can be found on the net. It's also not too difficult to obtain some similar code from Chrome's devtools.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/archive/v_0.0.10.tar.gz", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free", "keywords": "machine translation,free,scraping", "license": "MIT License", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "baidu-tr-free", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/baidu-tr-free/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/baidu-tr-free/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/archive/v_0.0.10.tar.gz", "Homepage": "http://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/baidu-tr-free/0.0.10/", "requires_dist": ["requests-cache", "js2py", "jsonpath-rw", "tqdm", "httpx", "requests", "browser-cookie3 (>=0.10.1)", "jmespath", "loguru", "pyquery"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "baidu translate for free", "version": "0.0.10", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>baidu-tr-free <img alt=\"Python3.6 package\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/eaba5a50c4219b39f629b3cd6fa44a9663323d1b/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f66667265656d742f62616964752d74722d667265652f776f726b666c6f77732f507974686f6e332e362532307061636b6167652f62616467652e737667\"><img alt=\"Codecov\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/25dadcdf1e02e10281de09900076f58d3c053dee/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f66667265656d742f62616964752d74722d667265652f776f726b666c6f77732f436f6465636f762f62616467652e737667\"><a href=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/baidu-tr-free\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"PyPI version\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/cce4cf58df6f84e63a0eb44ffc690b08f8c4c361/68747470733a2f2f62616467652e667572792e696f2f70792f62616964752d74722d667265652e737667\"></a></h1>\n<p>Baidu translate for free -- local cache plus throttling. Let's hope it lasts.</p>\n<h3>Broken or not</h3>\n<p><img alt=\"Python3.6 package\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/eaba5a50c4219b39f629b3cd6fa44a9663323d1b/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f66667265656d742f62616964752d74722d667265652f776f726b666c6f77732f507974686f6e332e362532307061636b6167652f62616467652e737667\">: failing indicates <code>broken</code>. In case of <code>failing</code>, try the following workaround: log in to <a href=\"https://passport.baidu.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://passport.baidu.com</a> first. Then use the Chrome browser to visit <a href=\"https://fanyi.baidu.com/v2transapi?from=en&amp;to=zh&amp;query=test\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://fanyi.baidu.com/v2transapi?from=en&amp;to=zh&amp;query=test</a>, press F12 and then ctr-R (or any method) to open devtools' Network tab and reload. Locate <code>https://fanyi.baidu.com/v2transapi?from=en&amp;to=zh</code> and obtain the BAIDUID and token strings in the headers. Plug in the BAIDUID and token strings to lines 66-67 in the  file <code>bdtr.py.</code></p>\n<h3>Fixed</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Text longer than 30 characters can be handled now.</li>\n<li>Auto-fetching BAIDUID and TOKEN</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Installation</h3>\n<p><code>pip install -U baidu-tr-free</code>\nor</p>\n<ul>\n<li>install (pip or whatever) necessary requirements, e.g. <code>pip install js2py requests_cache jsonpath_rw</code> or <code>pip install -r requirements.txt</code></li>\n<li>Drop the file bdtr.py in any folder in your PYTHONPATH (check with import sys; print(sys.path)\n<ul>\n<li>Several valid TOKEN/BAIDUID are included.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>or clone the repo (e.g., <code>git clone https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free.git</code> or download <a href=\"https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/archive/master.zip\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/ffreemt/baidu-tr-free/archive/master.zip</a> and unzip) and change to the baidu-tr-free folder and do a <code>python setup.py develop</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Usage</h3>\n<p>Log in to <a href=\"https://passport.baidu.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://passport.baidu.com</a>  using Chrome: <code>bdtr</code> needs the cookies info (<code>BAIDUID</code>) from the Chrome browser on baidu.com.</p>\n<pre><code>from bdtr import bdtr\nprint(bdtr('hello world'))  # -&gt; '\u4f60\u597d\uff0c\u4e16\u754c'\nprint(bdtr('hello world', to_lang='de'))  # -&gt;'Hallo Welt'\nprint(bdtr('hello world', to_lang='jp'))  # -&gt;'\u30cf\u30ed\u30fc\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9'\n</code></pre>\n<p><code>to_lang='fr'</code> does not seem to work tho.</p>\n<h3>Validation and Pressure Tests</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>pip install pytest</li>\n<li>pytest\n<ul>\n<li>Average delay for throttling set to 0.6 s, ajdust as needed</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Acknowledgments</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Thanks to everyone whose code was used</li>\n<li>JS_SIGN (javascript code for signing) can be found on the net. It's also not too difficult to obtain some similar code from Chrome's devtools.</li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6716431, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "21626c753bbaa6efdce03396598be834", "sha256"